Response to
Episode 7 - "The Clean Room"
@-------------------------------------------------
I think it's really cool how Patterson's initial goal/project was to determine the age of the earth and when he did after like 6 years of working really hard to sterilize his lab and instruments, he was able to accomplish something else which was end the use of lead in consumer products. I also find it kind of bizarre that the use of lead in consumer products only ended very recently. The Romans literally used tons of it in their everyday lives and even they knew it was toxic and the use of it continued into the twentieth century on a very wide scale but its toxicity was hidden to the public because lead is where the money came from which shows how messed up come peoples' priorities were. I just think it must've been really satisfying for Patterson to finally find out the age of the earth and get lead to be banned from being put into consumer products after years of fighting people who were way more powerful than him.
