Response to
Episode 8 - "Sisters of the Sun"
@-------------------------------------------------
I just think that what Cannon and Leavitt did was so amazing despite all their obstacles of having hearing loss and being discriminated against because they had a team of women, the "Harvard Computers". Also being very welcoming with Payne who was able to determine the temperature of the stars with their help (even though it was kind of disappointing that her theory was questioned and she ended up doubting herself). What they did as a team and individually was so great that it's disappointing that they don't have as much recognition as other groups of scientists because they were all women. Also with the huge supernovas that were in the episode, I wonder if any of them will be big enough to feel from earth, even though we won't feel the hypernova of Eta Carina, it would still be cool if we could actually see it even if it's so far into the future. 
