Response to
Episode 10 - "The Electric Boy"
@-------------------------------------------------
I think Michael Faraday's discoveries and conclusions about electricity and the earth's magnetic field are really cool and have such a greater impact in our health and the movement of the planets than what I knew before watching this episode. The episode emphasized how Faraday worked up from the poverty he was in in his childhood so I think that it was really impressive that he was able to conduct so many experiments over and over again and was able to solve the problem Newton couldn't despite not having a complete education. I didn't know that the earth's magnetic field helps in preventing cosmic rays from harming us and I also didn't know how it also was the reason why planets move around the sun because the sun, in some way, is still "touching" the planets. I also didn't know the impact of his discoveries until it was used to explain how we can communicate on such a major way we do today, even when people are thousands of miles away. 
